# UI Design-System Enforcement

This rule applies to all User Interface (UI) work in this repository.

## Non-negotiable defaults

- Do not create new local style variants for existing motifs.
- Reuse canonical components/tokens for:
  - buttons
  - circles/chips/badges
  - cards/surfaces
  - arrows/connectors
  - common form controls
- Prefer composition over one-off styling.
- Avoid inline motif styling when a shared motif exists.

## Required workflow for UI changes

1. Audit existing motif/component usage in touched areas.
2. Identify canonical component(s) and use them.
3. If duplicates exist, standardize to one shared component first (or in the same change when small).
4. Apply feature changes only after canonical path is clear.
5. Keep behavior unchanged unless explicitly requested.

## Exception protocol (mandatory)

- If a requested UI change cannot use canonical motifs/components, the agent must ask for an explicit exception before implementing a local variant.
- Exception request must include:
  - why canonical reuse is blocked
  - scope of proposed exception
  - rollback plan to return to canonical design system

## Completion checks

- Verify no new avoidable motif duplication was introduced in touched files.
- Confirm lints/types are clean for touched files.
- Summarize which canonical components were reused or standardized.
